Resizing: If you want to resize/reshape tensor, you can use torch.view:

x = torch.randn(4, 4)
y = x.view(16)
z = x.view(-1, 8)   # the size -1 is inferred from other dimensions
print(x.size(), y.size(), z.size())

Out:

torch.Size([4, 4]) torch.Size([16]) torch.Size([2, 8])


